In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims December 15, 2013, as Bill of Rights Day in the United States. The Bill of Rights is seen as the foundation of American liberty, protecting fundamental rights such as freedom of speech, assembly, and religion, as well as ensuring justice under the law. The President highlights the importance of the Bill of Rights in shaping American society and driving progress, including the fight for equality and civil rights. He calls upon the people of the United States to commemorate this observance with appropriate ceremonies and activities.